[~kgill] When describe-load-balancer-policies is called *without* ELB name, it will return the policies seeded in the system which is available for usage. Then one can create a policy with 'Reference-Security-Policy' attribute set to one of the available policy. For example,

{code}
{ "PolicyName" : "mypol",
  "PolicyTypeName" : "SSLNegotiationPolicyType",
   "PolicyAttributeDescriptions": [
                {
                    "AttributeName": "Reference-Security-Policy",
                    "AttributeValue": "ELBSecurityPolicy-2015-05"
                } ]
}
{code}

[~spark]: Got it.  Any idea how to issue a describe-load-balancer-policies API call via Boto?  I'm using the following, but it returns an empty result...

{code}
from boto.ec2.elb.policies import OtherPolicy
# ...
elb_conn.get_object('DescribeLoadBalancerPolicies', {}, OtherPolicy)
{code}
